LEGAL NOTICE

Michael Toikach, et al. v. Christian Dior, Inc.

Case No. CACE 25-18776

Circuit Court for Broward County, Florida

IF YOU WERE NOTIFIED THAT YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION MAY HAVE BEEN=20
ACCESSED IN THE JANUARY 2025 CHRISTIAN DIOR DATA INCIDENT,

YOU MAY BE ENTITLED TO BENEFITS FROM A CLASS ACTION SETTLEMENT.

A court has authorized this notice. This is not a solicitation from a=20
lawyer.

You are not being sued.

Please read this Notice carefully and completely.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------=
-----

Your Unique ID: 92-H2VQYM-77

Your PIN: 574369

Dear Daniyah Ramay Taimur:

A Settlement has been reached with Christian Dior, Inc. ("Dior") in a=20
class action lawsuit about a cybersecurity incident that occurred in=20
January 2025, in which an unauthorized party was able to gain access to=20
a Dior database that contained information about Dior clients (the "Data=20
Incident").

Dior denies that it did anything wrong, and the Court has not decided=20
who is right. The parties have agreed to settle the lawsuit=20
("Settlement") to avoid the risks, disruption, and uncertainties of=20
continued litigation.

A copy of the Settlement is available at www.cddatasettlement.com

http://www.cddatasettlement.com

.

Who is included in the Settlement? The Court has defined the class as:=20
"All U.S. individuals who were sent notice by Defendant that their=20
Personal Information may have been impacted in the Data Incident."

The Court has appointed experienced attorneys, called Class Counsel, to=20
represent the Class.

What are the Settlement benefits? You can claim two years of Credit=20
Monitoring (at no cost to you). Additionally , you may claim up to=20
$1,500.00 for reimbursement of qualifying documented losses for eligible=20
out-of-pocket expenses.

Full details and instructions are available online and in the Long Form=20
Notice.

How do I receive a benefit? Visit www.cddatasettlement.com

http://www.cddatasettlement.com

to submit your claim.

To receive a paper copy and submit by U.S. Mail, call 1-888-836-1708, or=20
email your request to info@cddatasettlement.com

mailto:info@cddatasettlement.com

. Claims must be submitted online, mailed, or emailed by May 25, 2026 .

Your Unique ID: 92-H2VQYM-77

Your PIN: 574369

What if I don't want to participate in the Settlement? If you do not=20
want to be legally bound by the Settlement, you must exclude yourself by=20
May 25, 2026 or you will not be able to sue Dior for the claims made in=20
this lawsuit. If you exclude yourself, you cannot get benefits from this=20
Settlement. If you want to object to the Settlement, you may file an=20
objection by May 25, 2026 . The Settlement Agreement, available on the=20
Settlement website at www.cddatasettlement.com

http://www.cddatasettlement.com

, explains how to exclude yourself or object.

When will the Court decide whether to approve the Settlement? The Court=20
will hold a hearing in this case on June 22, 2026 at the Circuit Court=20
for Broward County, Florida (via Zoom), to consider whether to approve=20
the Settlement. The Court will also consider Class Counsel's request for=20
attorneys' fees and costs of up to $400,000.00, and $2,500.00 for the=20
Class Representatives. You may attend the hearing at your own cost, but=20
you do not have to.

This notice email is only a summary. For more information, call=20
1-888-836-1708 or click here: www.cddatasettlement.com

http://www.cddatasettlement.com

.

Class Member ID: 49829

If you do not wish to receive future emails, click here

